race.comment: SAKIMA (3) resumes and has switched from a leading Sydney stable to one of the best in Victoria. The speed-bred mare didn't come up last preparation but was Stakes placed on debut so has the class. She draws inside and has three jumpouts under the saddle. Has Tasmania's premiership hoop aboard and the betting will be key. ELENA MONTERO (5) led and won at Donald and then jumped again at a short quote beaten 2L at Albury. She's likely to jump and run from an inside barrier and fitter again is a decent chance to bounce. SURPRISATIC (7) brings two wins and a placing from her last three. Fully fit now and the inside barrier should advantage. Deserves plenty of consideration. PAPARAZZO (9) improved again missing a nose at Albury and the blinkers come off. Can't be ruled out. WRITTEN ROYALTY (1) is capable of featuring but gives away big starts and trust is required.
